accessibility.text: Here’s an example of how motions can conflict with each other. I’ve put these motions on a circle.  	On the right, the first-order motion is in the same direction as position-defined motion — they are congruent.

On the left, the position-defined motion is also counterclockwise, but the first-order motion is in the opposite direction — they are in conflict. While this stimulus appears to be less smooth and to have more flicker, you can see that the position-defined motion again “wins out” over the first-order motion.
